OL,3,CFormer Conservative MP quits party to
OL,4,Cjoin Reform UK
OL,6,FConservative leader Kemi Badenoch has
OL,7,Fpreviously been dismissive of Reform
OL,8,FUK defections, saying "If people
OL,9,Fcannot deal with tough times in
OL,10,Fopposition, they definitely will not
OL,11,Fbe able to deal with tough times in
OL,12,Fgovernment,"
OL,14,FShe told the BBC "(Reform) want more
OL,15,Fwelfare. We are not the welfare party.
OL,16,FWe're the Conservative Party, the
OL,17,Fparty of fiscal responsibility. If
OL,18,Fthey want to go to Reform so that they
OL,19,Fcan have more welfare, then maybe
OL,20,Fthat's the right place for them.
